cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.OO

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new object-oriented language for modeling hybrid systems, which is related to software engineering.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper focuses on modeling hybrid systems, which is a topic in systems and control.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes a new programming language, Apricot, which combines features of domain-specific and object-oriented languages.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the semantics of the Apricot language.
- cs.OO (Object-Oriented Programming) is relevant as the paper proposes an object-oriented language for modeling hybrid systems.
